1
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,400
<i>Is Pun interested in you?</i>

2
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:10,240
This one gets my approval.

3
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,840
Mom, that's a bit fast.

4
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:14,960
Then I must be someone special.

5
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:17,320
You could say that.

6
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:22,360
It's like you found the right person
at the wrong time.

7
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:25,480
If you find the wrong person
at the right time,

8
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,800
it's still wrong.

9
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:29,720
- What's your feeling for Pie?
- I'd like her to be my girlfriend.

10
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,080
<i>I like Pun.</i>

11
00:02:31,160 --> 00:02:33,480
If you're really
not interested, back off.

12
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,280
I'm serious about him.

13
00:02:35,880 --> 00:02:38,760
But if you want to compete with me,
then bring it on.

14
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:48,120
NAGOYA, JAPAN

15
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:02,040
Hello, Run. What's up?

16
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:03,960
What?

17
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:07,120
Boy's sick? Kim quit too?

18
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:09,760
Yeah. Can you help me out?

19
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,360
Well…

20
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,960
I was planning to head back
to Thailand for a month

21
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,480
before continuing my studies.

22
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:18,600
I haven't been back since I got here.

23
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,400
Come help me first, okay?

24
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:21,840
Have you paid for your flight yet?

25
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:25,000
If you have, I'll pay you back double.

26
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:28,680
Please, I really need help.
There are so many customers right now.

27
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:33,680
And if you come help me during this break,
I'll give you extra pay.

28
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:38,480
Really, Run?

29
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,680
Yeah, of course!

30
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:41,120
Excuse me.

31
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,680
Yes, one second.

32
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:45,840
I'm really in a tough spot.
Otherwise, I wouldn't be asking you.

33
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,640
- Excuse me.
- Yes.

34
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,560
Don't hang up yet!

35
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:51,040
Just give me a moment.

36
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,320
I'm coming!

37
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,240
Welcome!

38
00:03:58,320 --> 00:04:01,280
Cheers!

39
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,280
Your Pad Thai, sir.

40
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:05,680
Sorry for the wait.

41
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:07,880
Your Tom Yum Goong is ready.

42
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,600
Are you Thai?

43
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,640
Yes, I am.

44
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:15,120
Wow, you speak Japanese really well.

45
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,880
How long have you been working here?

46
00:04:17,480 --> 00:04:18,560
It's been a while now.

47
00:04:18,640 --> 00:04:19,959
I'm here to further my studies.

48
00:04:20,040 --> 00:04:21,800
Since I have some free time, I also work.

49
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,400
Wow.

50
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:27,920
You're saving up to ask a girl out, right?

51
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:31,160
If she's still waiting for me, then yes.

52
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,040
Is your next semester going to be tough?

53
00:04:39,880 --> 00:04:40,720
Well…

54
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:44,000
It's lighter than last semester,
mostly focusing on projects.

55
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,520
Can you be my manager?

56
00:04:47,760 --> 00:04:51,080
I'll give you a salary,
overtime pay, and a profit share.

57
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:53,680
I want to expand to Osaka.

58
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:56,040
I need to travel back and forth,
so I can't be here often.

59
00:04:56,120 --> 00:04:58,120
You have a lot of loyal customers.

60
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:00,440
You're good both front-of-house
and in the kitchen.

61
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:03,600
If you help me out,
I'll feel much more at ease.

62
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:05,040
Are you interested?

63
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,040
What do you think?

64
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:12,840
It's just a small token of appreciation.

65
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:16,080
If you accept the manager role,
we can start tomorrow.

66
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:17,520
Is that okay?

67
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:00,560
I'm giving my first month's salary to you.

68
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,320
Don't you keep some for yourself?

69
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,520
Mom.

70
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,000
Please accept it.

71
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,720
It may not be much,

72
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,440
but I really want to give it to you.

73
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:18,960
Mom.

74
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:22,640
You've taken such good care
of me all this time.

75
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:27,000
Now it's my turn to take care of you.

76
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:31,200
Thank you so much, my dear.

77
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,080
You're welcome.

78
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:42,480
You're such a good person.

79
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:44,560
You're a wonderful daughter.

80
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:50,120
One day, you'll get good things in return.

81
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:57,080
Believe in goodness

82
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:02,520
and you'll meet someone good
who truly deserves you.

83
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:09,960
Yes.

84
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:20,880
<i>Tomorrow, I'm going to study abroad.</i>

85
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,280
<i>Can I meet you today?</i>

86
00:07:26,640 --> 00:07:30,920
I'm sorry for the trouble
that I've caused you in the past.

87
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:36,320
And thank you
for speaking to me so honestly.

88
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:39,640
Even though it was harsh
and almost made me want to end my life,

89
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:41,760
I understand.

90
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,760
Thanking me or being sarcastic?

91
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,920
I'm serious.

92
00:07:48,280 --> 00:07:52,160
I've never met anyone
who speaks so bluntly like you.

93
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:55,640
I really like…

94
00:07:57,280 --> 00:07:59,080
and admire you.

95
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,560
Even though you've never

96
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:05,520
felt the same way about me,

97
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,880
but I want you to be happy.

98
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:11,720
I want you to be with someone good.

99
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:16,320
Someone who's not Pie,
because she's not good enough.

100
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:19,880
Mink, saying that isn't very nice.

101
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:22,160
Show some respect for Pie.

102
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:25,480
You've always spoken bluntly with me.

103
00:08:25,560 --> 00:08:28,280
I'll be blunt with you too.
It's only fair, right?

104
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:32,840
Okay, maybe my standards are high.

105
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:35,120
But if you're going to reject me,

106
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,840
at least pick someone better than me.

107
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:40,159
Pie isn't the good person
you think she is.

108
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,520
Thanks for telling me, Mink.

109
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,520
But I'll have to disagree.

110
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:47,640
I'm confident that I know Pie well enough.

111
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:54,720
I hope you really do know her well.

112
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:02,000
That's all I wanted to say.

113
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:06,160
I hope you're happy
with whom you've chosen.

114
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,200
Good luck.

115
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,360
I wish you the best too, Mink.

116
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,920
And I hope you're happy
with the choice you make.

117
00:09:55,440 --> 00:10:00,840
ONE YEAR LATER

118
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:05,240
Hey!

119
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:09,720
This is Tay, my boyfriend!

120
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:10,640
Huh?

121
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,400
- This is Pie, right?
- Hi.

122
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:14,280
Krarok talks about you all the time.

123
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:16,320
Oh, really?

124
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:17,760
What does she gossip about me?

125
00:10:17,840 --> 00:10:20,240
No gossip at all.
She always speaks highly of you.

126
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:24,320
She's a really kind person,
never mean to anyone.

127
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:27,600
Since I've been with her,
I've never heard her speak ill of anyone.

128
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:30,680
You've been secretly observing me?

129
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:32,160
I didn't even notice.

130
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,880
You're quite observant, huh?

131
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,240
Rok. It's almost 1 p.m.

132
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:39,360
I need to work,
and I haven't ordered my coffee.

133
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,960
Just order. You can order from Tay.

134
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:45,320
He owns the shop and is also the barista.

135
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:47,320
- Just tell him what you want.
- That's right.

136
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:51,680
Then I'll have this one.

137
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:53,800
Got it. I'll make it right away.

138
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,000
Thanks.

139
00:10:57,920 --> 00:11:00,640
Hey. Rok.

140
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:02,440
- What's this about?
- Huh?

141
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:05,200
Are you kidding? Where did you meet him?

142
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:08,400
We met during
the last mountain biking trip.

143
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,360
He fell off his bike.

144
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:13,360
I helped carry his bike down.

145
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:16,080
Then he fell for how strong I was.

146
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,040
And we became a couple.

147
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,960
That was pretty quick, don't you think?

148
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,120
Pie!

149
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:25,000
When it's the right person,
you don't need time.

150
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,080
If it's the right person, it just works.

151
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:38,800
That's true.

152
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,880
Don't cry, sweetheart.

153
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:00,200
The whiny singer's here.

154
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:03,040
She's not giving up the mic.
Looks like she'll sing for a while.

155
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:04,800
You're teasing the kid.

156
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,400
Isn't it true?

157
00:12:06,480 --> 00:12:09,160
Handling kids is harder
than dealing with old aunties.

158
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:10,880
- I hate kids.
- What?

159
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:16,320
I'll buy a new one for you.

160
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:17,720
Why are you crying?

161
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,160
I don't know what's going on today.

162
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:22,520
Vivi's being fussy. I'll take her home.

163
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:25,160
It's okay. I understand.
Kids are like that.

164
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,160
We'll reschedule.

165
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,360
I'm really sorry, we didn't get to talk.

166
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:30,200
You can leave Vivi with me.

167
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:31,840
That way, you can continue the work.

168
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:34,960
No, I want to go home.

169
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:38,560
But there are frogs here!

170
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:40,800
Want to see them?

171
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,760
- Let's play with it together.
- Let's!

172
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:50,040
Do it like this. One, two, three.

173
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:52,520
Got it?

174
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:58,120
I got it.

175
00:12:58,200 --> 00:13:01,000
Let's duel. It's not jumping, Vivi.

176
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,280
One, two, three.

177
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:04,680
- The frog jumps!
- The frog jumps!

178
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:06,720
Do you know that this frog can even fly?

179
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:07,800
Look.

180
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:13,480
Your assistant is really good.

181
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:15,200
Vivi stopped crying right away.

182
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:17,040
Guess she has a kid.

183
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,400
Not yet. She's still single.

184
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:27,720
- We should get back to business. This way.
- Sure, sounds good.

185
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:56,040
Oops, almost ripped.

186
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,440
<i>You had a miscarriage.</i>

187
00:14:02,080 --> 00:14:03,880
You have to be strong.

188
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:06,840
The baby is at peace now.

189
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,520
But right now,

190
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,400
you need to take care of yourself

191
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,040
<i>and get strong.</i>

192
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,040
Here.

193
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:25,880
I'll review the design one more time
and then update you.

194
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:28,280
Sure. Let's set up an appointment later.

195
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,320
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

196
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:30,400
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

197
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:31,760
- Bye.
- Bye.

198
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,560
Don't forget to show it to your mom.

199
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:35,960
- Bye.
- Bye.

200
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:45,040
Being an only child, how come
you're so good with kids?

201
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,520
I know, right? I'm not sure either.

202
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,000
I don't really play with kids much.

203
00:14:53,080 --> 00:14:55,840
But when I saw her crying earlier,
I felt sorry for her.

204
00:14:55,920 --> 00:14:57,280
I saw her wearing a frog shirt,

205
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:59,440
so I thought she might like frogs.

206
00:14:59,520 --> 00:15:01,040
I just kind of guessed.

207
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:07,080
Have you ever thought about having kids?

208
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:16,240
If it happens when I'm ready,
I'd love to have kids.

209
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:20,840
But I'm not sure
if I'll ever be ready to be a mom.

210
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:26,080
If I'm still figuring things out,
I don't want to think about it yet.

211
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,920
It feels far off.

212
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,400
I think it's not so far off.

213
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,000
If you're not ready yet,

214
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,920
but you meet someone who is,

215
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:44,760
sometimes things that feel far away
might not be as far as you think.

216
00:16:24,960 --> 00:16:26,520
Surprise!

217
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:30,600
- What are you hiding, Pie?
- Nothing.

218
00:16:30,680 --> 00:16:32,920
- If it's nothing, then let me see.
- Hey, no!

219
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,240
You don't need to look!

220
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:36,040
You keep secrets from your friend?

221
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:38,120
No, but you don't need to look!

222
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:40,480
- No, I'm going to look!
- Hey, no! Rok!

223
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,960
- Rok!
- You have to let me see.

224
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:45,840
A scholarship application
for studying in Australia.

225
00:16:46,960 --> 00:16:48,840
Pie, you're applying for a scholarship?

226
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:53,600
Did Pie say where she's going?

227
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,160
Melbourne, Australia.

228
00:16:55,240 --> 00:16:57,560
I got her to admit she's applying
for a master's scholarship.

229
00:16:57,640 --> 00:16:58,840
Full-ride scholarship.

230
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,200
She'll work
and send money to her mom.

231
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:03,560
She's already contacted
two Thai restaurants there.

232
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,760
She's calculated
that she'll make more money there

233
00:17:05,839 --> 00:17:07,720
than working with you.

234
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:14,160
If they accept her,
she's definitely going.

235
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:16,640
So,

236
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:20,400
Pie's really planning to go
without telling me?

237
00:17:21,599 --> 00:17:24,160
I think the reason she didn't tell you
is because she knew

238
00:17:24,240 --> 00:17:25,720
that no one would let her go.

239
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,319
Maybe even Aunt Tubtim doesn't know.

240
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:29,600
Because if she did,
she wouldn't let her go.

241
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,680
I wouldn't let her go either.

242
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:43,080
Yes, Mom?

243
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:47,040
Pie! The watch I gave you
for your birthday, do you have it?

244
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,080
Yes.

245
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,520
I'm not waiting any longer!

246
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,680
Wait a minute, please!

247
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,080
I'll go in myself.

248
00:17:52,160 --> 00:17:54,400
- Pie, sell it now!
- Please wait!

249
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:57,760
- You can't get in!
- They're about to take my car!

250
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:59,200
Sell it now!

251
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:02,520
Okay, Mom. I'll go right away.
Talk to you later.

252
00:18:08,440 --> 00:18:10,600
- Pie. Pie.
- Yes?

253
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:14,360
- I need to talk to you.
- Sorry, Pun. Is it urgent?

254
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,600
It's not urgent, but it's important.

255
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,320
If it's not urgent, then I'm sorry.

256
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:19,720
I really can't talk right now.

257
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:21,200
I'd like to take a half-day off.

258
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:23,480
Wait, Pie.

259
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:25,840
What's going on?

260
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:27,640
You seem flustered.

261
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:31,440
Hey, you can tell me. In case I can help.

262
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:33,760
It's nothing, Pun. I can handle it.

263
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:34,800
I really need to go now.

264
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,200
Pie!

265
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,480
I'm your boss.

266
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:40,280
If you don't tell me,
I won't approve your leave.

267
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:50,280
Tell me. What's going on?
Where are you going?

268
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:52,120
Well…

269
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:57,520
I'm going to the pawn shop.

270
00:18:59,240 --> 00:19:00,960
- Give it to me!
- No way!

271
00:19:01,040 --> 00:19:02,680
Let go of me! I won't give it to you.

272
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:04,440
- Madam!
- Where are you going?

273
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:06,920
- No, stop!
- You're being so difficult!

274
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:08,200
Don't touch my mom!

275
00:19:08,280 --> 00:19:09,480
- Get out, right now!
- Pie!

276
00:19:09,560 --> 00:19:12,280
Get out of my house! Get out!

277
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:13,320
You get out!

278
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,680
Pie!

279
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:20,440
Miss Pie!

280
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:22,440
Pie!

281
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:24,040
Hey, come here!

282
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,280
Let go! Pie, my dear!

283
00:19:28,360 --> 00:19:30,520
- Pie, are you okay?
- Mom.

284
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,840
Oh no, Pie!

285
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:34,080
You're bleeding!

286
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,320
- Mom, are you okay?
- I'm fine.

287
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:39,320
- Does it hurt a lot?
- Did you get the money?!

288
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,880
If not, I'm not waiting!

289
00:19:40,960 --> 00:19:42,640
- I don't have it! Ugh!
- Give me the key!

290
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:45,080
- Mom!
- You're quite the debt collector.

291
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,400
Look, her head is split open.

292
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:48,880
- I don't care!
- You still dare to demand money?

293
00:19:48,960 --> 00:19:51,480
- I don't care! Give me the key!
- Don't touch my mom! Let go!

294
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,920
If you want money,
stop hurting these women!

295
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,840
You broke into someone else's house
without consent.

296
00:19:57,920 --> 00:20:01,360
That's illegal
under sections 362, 363, and 364.

297
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:02,880
Assaulting someone
and destroying property.

298
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:05,320
Section 359 of the Criminal Code.

299
00:20:05,400 --> 00:20:07,840
That's up to two years in prison
or a fine of up to 200,000 baht.

300
00:20:07,920 --> 00:20:11,600
I have video evidence
of everything you've done.

301
00:20:11,680 --> 00:20:13,360
- Stop filming!
- Hey!

302
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:14,560
- Stop!
- Why can't we film?

303
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:15,920
- It's our right!
- If you don't stop,

304
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,680
- I'll sue you for sure.
- Stop filming!

305
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:20,680
And you won't get this money.

306
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:24,880
The money in this envelope

307
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:28,480
is old debt combined with
the new payment.

308
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:29,840
I've cleared it all up.

309
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,880
But according
to the loan documents I've seen,

310
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:35,920
you've charged a 20% interest rate,
which is illegal.

311
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:39,360
The maximum interest rate is 15% per year.

312
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:42,560
Then you come to collect debts,
using violence and insulting language.

313
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,960
This could mean one year in prison
and a fine of up to 100,000 baht.

314
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,760
If you don't want to be prosecuted,

315
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:49,840
go back and tell your boss

316
00:20:49,920 --> 00:20:51,840
that I've calculated the remaining debt,

317
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:55,920
deducting the interest
based on the legal maximum.

318
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,160
If your boss has any issues,
they can speak with my lawyer anytime.

319
00:20:59,240 --> 00:21:00,280
Is that clear?

320
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,080
Got it?

321
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:15,360
I'm sorry, Pie.

322
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,120
Does it hurt a lot?

323
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:20,720
Not much, Pun.
It just startled me. Sorry about that.

324
00:21:21,800 --> 00:21:23,040
You got startled?

325
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,880
- Pun, I'll give you my watch for now.
- Yes?

326
00:21:30,960 --> 00:21:33,720
The rest, you can deduct from my salary.

327
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,960
I'll try to pay you back
as soon as possible.

328
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:38,360
It's okay.

329
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:40,960
I'm not in a hurry for the money.

330
00:21:42,640 --> 00:21:45,120
But I don't feel good about it, Pun.

331
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:49,520
You had to spend money, waste time,

332
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:51,480
and do something risky like that earlier.

333
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,960
I feel really bad about it.

334
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,440
Pie.

335
00:22:01,040 --> 00:22:02,480
But I actually feel good about it.

336
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:10,520
I've never protected or taken care
of anyone like this before.

337
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:15,440
While I was doing it, I secretly thought

338
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:17,160
that I'm kind of cool.

339
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:30,320
But I'm serious, Pie.

340
00:22:31,480 --> 00:22:32,960
I really feel good

341
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,800
about helping you and your mom.

342
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:40,360
It's also made me get to know you better.

343
00:22:50,920 --> 00:22:52,800
- Let me.
- Yes.

344
00:22:55,160 --> 00:22:56,240
Does it hurt?

345
00:23:02,280 --> 00:23:03,560
Oh my gosh!

346
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:09,880
I never imagined in my life
that a good man would offer to help me.

347
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:12,120
My whole life, since I was born,

348
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:14,360
it's always been men
taking advantage of me.

349
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:18,280
Mr. Pun is really cool.

350
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:20,080
So clever!

351
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:22,600
He lied to those guys,
saying he was livestreaming.

352
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:25,280
But I saw it. He didn't
even have his phone on!

353
00:23:25,360 --> 00:23:28,480
I'm not sure if what he said was true,

354
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:30,400
but it was really convincing.

355
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:32,160
Some of it is true, some of it's not.

356
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:35,560
I just said what my lawyer recommended.

357
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:37,280
But I only said what I remembered.

358
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:41,680
Even if I said something wrong,
they probably wouldn't know.

359
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:46,240
- Pun.
- Yes?

360
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:51,240
I don't even know how to thank you
for helping my family this much.

361
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:55,840
I've already told you,
I feel good doing this.

362
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,920
Actually, I should thank you too,

363
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:03,840
for showing me

364
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:06,160
that I also have this side to me.

365
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:13,120
Come here. I'll bandage your wound.

366
00:24:14,480 --> 00:24:16,080
Thank you.

367
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:24,120
All done.

368
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:28,760
Pun.

369
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:34,040
Now you know

370
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:37,000
that my family is not perfect.

371
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:46,160
I haven't been hiding our poverty
or using brand names

372
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:48,000
to make people think we're rich.

373
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:53,600
But it's for my mom's peace of mind.

374
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:01,360
Everything she had since she was young,

375
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:06,560
when she lost it, she couldn't handle it.

376
00:25:09,520 --> 00:25:11,840
I've tried to get her to accept the truth.

377
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:16,200
But every time we talked,
we ended up arguing.

378
00:25:20,160 --> 00:25:23,600
Now I understand.

379
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:27,720
It's her happiness.

380
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:31,680
And I don't want to hurt her.

381
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,360
That's why I told you before

382
00:25:42,280 --> 00:25:45,000
that I'm not good

383
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:47,320
and I'm not perfect.

384
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:51,720
I still have a lot of flaws.

385
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:54,720
This is just part of it.

386
00:26:06,440 --> 00:26:07,720
Thank you, Pie,

387
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:11,520
for trusting me and sharing this with me.

388
00:26:14,560 --> 00:26:16,960
I'm glad to know this version of you.

389
00:26:18,600 --> 00:26:20,320
And I'm not disappointed at all.

390
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:23,400
I still feel the same way about you.

391
00:26:25,120 --> 00:26:26,360
Nothing's changed.

392
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:35,520
Now, give me a smile.

393
00:26:40,800 --> 00:26:42,600
- You're back, dear?
- Yes.

394
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:45,200
Come say hi to Charlotte,
Aunt Chuen's daughter.

395
00:26:45,280 --> 00:26:46,520
Hello!

396
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,360
Hello.

397
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:55,320
She moved to L.A. when she was a kid,
graduated, and just came back.

398
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:58,280
When you have time,
take her out for a bit.

399
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:06,000
I'm really sorry,
but I'm busy with work right now.

400
00:27:06,520 --> 00:27:07,600
I can't take you out.

401
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:11,680
Excuse me.

402
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:17,520
Ask Pun first before arranging anything.

403
00:27:18,040 --> 00:27:18,880
Why ask?

404
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:21,680
Pun listens to me.

405
00:27:21,760 --> 00:27:23,280
He does whatever I say.

406
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:34,240
Go buy something for Pun, okay?
He helped us a lot.

407
00:27:34,320 --> 00:27:35,480
Yes!

408
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:37,960
I passed!

409
00:27:38,680 --> 00:27:40,280
Passed what, Pie?

410
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:49,920
I won't let you go.

411
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:51,680
No matter what, I won't let you go.

412
00:27:52,200 --> 00:27:55,000
Last time you went to Mae Hong Son,

413
00:27:55,080 --> 00:27:56,800
when you came back, you had nothing left.

414
00:27:56,880 --> 00:27:58,040
Now you want to go to Australia.

415
00:27:58,120 --> 00:27:59,560
What will be left when you get back?

416
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:01,240
But I want to go, Mom.

417
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:04,080
If I pursue my master's,
I can get a much higher salary.

418
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:06,720
While studying, I'll work
and send money back to you.

419
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:09,920
Mom, if you don't trust me,
we can go together.

420
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:12,120
We can sell the house, the car,
everything, and go together.

421
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:15,120
Are you crazy, Pie? How can we do that?

422
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:17,120
My friends will gossip,
saying we've hit hard times

423
00:28:17,200 --> 00:28:19,680
and sold everything to go live there.

424
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:21,360
Why care about what they say, Mom?

425
00:28:21,440 --> 00:28:23,280
I'm going to work honestly.

426
00:28:23,360 --> 00:28:25,120
I want to pay Pun back quickly.

427
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:26,840
I don't want to owe him for long.

428
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:27,920
Mom.

429
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:31,880
Please let me go. Please.

430
00:28:31,960 --> 00:28:35,040
Mom, I'm begging you. Please let me go.

431
00:28:35,120 --> 00:28:37,960
Fine, if you really want to go that badly,

432
00:28:38,040 --> 00:28:40,680
just go. You don't need to ask me.

433
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:43,440
You've never cared about me anyway.

434
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:49,080
Mom…

435
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:54,800
Last time, you made plans behind my back.

436
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:58,120
This time, you secretly applied
without telling me.

437
00:28:58,200 --> 00:29:01,400
Now they've accepted you,
and you're cornering me like this.

438
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:03,120
Why are you asking me?

439
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:05,760
If you want to leave me,
just leave already.

440
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:09,000
I'm not leaving you.
I'm just going to study.

441
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:14,520
Mom, I want our lives to get better.

442
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:17,240
I promise I'll take care of myself.

443
00:29:19,960 --> 00:29:21,960
I really need to go, Mom.

444
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:24,680
I won't make mistakes like that again.

445
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:30,000
No matter what, I'm going.

446
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,840
RESIGNATION LETTER

447
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:39,920
Are you quitting?

448
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:42,160
Did you get the scholarship, Pie?

449
00:29:42,240 --> 00:29:44,200
Yeah, I found out this morning.

450
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:45,920
Did your mom agree?

451
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:47,840
I'll go, even if she doesn't.

452
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:49,640
Have you told Pun yet?

453
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:57,280
Pie didn't tell me,
but I found out from Rok.

454
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:01,760
And how Rok found out was by accident.

455
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:04,280
You don't want Pie to go, do you?

456
00:30:05,840 --> 00:30:06,840
No, I don't.

457
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:11,560
So, what should we do
to change Pie's mind?

458
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:15,760
From what I know of Pie,
if she goes to study abroad this time,

459
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:18,560
I'm sure she won't come back.

460
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:21,960
She'll probably find a job and stay there.

461
00:30:23,920 --> 00:30:24,960
Pun.

462
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:28,000
I'll be blunt with you.

463
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:33,000
I can tell how you feel about Pie.

464
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:41,680
If Pie really goes to study,
do you think you'll wait for her?

465
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:46,680
I really don't want to say this.

466
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:49,640
But I feel sorry
for someone as good as you.

467
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:53,600
And I probably can't stop her from going.

468
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:56,040
But if it's you,

469
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,760
you might be able to change her mind.

470
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:03,080
And if you really don't want her to go,

471
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,560
you'll have to do something about it.

472
00:31:06,160 --> 00:31:09,360
Because if she goes this time,

473
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:11,920
she's not coming back for sure.

474
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:27,040
- Pie.
- Yes?

475
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:28,920
This is the first draft
of the Virtual Museum 3D.

476
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:33,440
I'd like you to try it out and tell me

477
00:31:33,520 --> 00:31:35,360
if it feels like
you're really in a museum.

478
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:36,280
Sure.

479
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:39,960
Okay.

480
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:42,840
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

481
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:58,720
What kind of museum is this?
Why does it feel so empty?

482
00:31:59,520 --> 00:32:01,400
Try opening the door and see.

483
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,520
Okay.

484
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:45,360
Pun, is this really the company project?

485
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:59,840
THANK YOU FOR COMING INTO MY LIFE

486
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:27,240
Pie.

487
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:35,840
Do you know

488
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:40,560
it's really hard to find a flower

489
00:33:41,640 --> 00:33:43,000
that perfectly fits the vase?

490
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:45,720
And when you do find it,

491
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,840
you don't want to let it slip away.

492
00:33:52,200 --> 00:33:53,840
Just like how I found you.

493
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,520
So, what you showed me earlier

494
00:33:59,280 --> 00:34:01,680
isn't related to work, right?

495
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:06,720
Everything I've said

496
00:34:07,840 --> 00:34:09,480
leads up to this.

497
00:34:12,199 --> 00:34:13,159
I see.

498
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:18,040
I know you got a scholarship
to study abroad.

499
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,639
I don't want you to go.

500
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,800
I'm afraid you won't come back.

501
00:34:26,120 --> 00:34:28,840
But I'm not stopping you.

502
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:33,480
If you're still set on going,

503
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:35,719
I'll go with you.

504
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:36,679
Huh?

505
00:34:38,719 --> 00:34:39,960
I'll find a job there.

506
00:34:41,760 --> 00:34:43,360
Would that be okay, Pun?

507
00:34:43,440 --> 00:34:44,480
Of course.

508
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:47,320
Australia with you there

509
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:49,840
sounds great to me.

510
00:34:58,880 --> 00:35:03,720
You might be confused
as to why I'm being so direct.

511
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:06,680
But everything I've said

512
00:35:07,880 --> 00:35:10,200
isn't just a momentary feeling.

513
00:35:11,880 --> 00:35:14,920
We've known each other for a while.

514
00:35:15,560 --> 00:35:18,440
I've tried asking you out several times.

515
00:35:20,000 --> 00:35:21,480
You didn't seem to notice.

516
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:24,800
Or maybe you did,

517
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:27,280
but pretended not to.

518
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:32,480
I don't want to waste any more time.

519
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:37,080
I want you in my life.

520
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:48,160
I feel at ease when I'm with you.

521
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:53,120
I like how you're different
from everyone else.

522
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:58,000
I think we're like a flower and a vase.

523
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,840
And we fit together

524
00:36:03,680 --> 00:36:06,920
too well to just be coworkers.

525
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:14,160
Can we be more than that?

526
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:28,440
You don't have to answer right away.

527
00:36:30,280 --> 00:36:32,120
I'll give you time to think.

528
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:37,080
But not too long. Okay?

529
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:42,480
Okay.

530
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:47,160
I'll be waiting for good news.

531
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:58,240
- Pie, how's it going?
- Hello.

532
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:59,360
What do you mean, Mom?

533
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,680
Well, how's it going with Pun?

534
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:05,080
Oh, so you talked to Pun.

535
00:37:05,160 --> 00:37:06,760
That's why he asked to be my boyfriend?

536
00:37:06,840 --> 00:37:08,400
And what did you say to him?

537
00:37:08,480 --> 00:37:11,720
I haven't answered him yet. It's too soon.

538
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:15,520
With a good person
you've known for a year or two,

539
00:37:15,600 --> 00:37:18,800
you say it's too soon, but with that guy,
after meeting for just a few days,

540
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:21,080
you already got involved.
Isn't that too soon, Pie?

541
00:37:21,160 --> 00:37:22,840
Mom!

542
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:25,600
I'm just worried about you, Pie.

543
00:37:25,680 --> 00:37:27,680
I don't want you
to miss out on someone good.

544
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:30,800
If you want a good life,
you need to be with good people.

545
00:37:30,880 --> 00:37:33,760
And on top of that,
Pun has been helping our family a lot.

546
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:35,520
What more do you need to think about?

547
00:37:45,120 --> 00:37:46,520
Pie.

548
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,720
Please don't go.

549
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:53,200
I have no one left.

550
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:56,760
Your dad left me.
Pie, please don't leave me too.

551
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:59,760
I'm begging you. Stay with me, Pie.

552
00:38:00,560 --> 00:38:04,440
Please don't leave me.
I really have no one left, Pie.

553
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:33,120
Hello. This is Saensuk Homestay.

554
00:38:33,840 --> 00:38:34,840
It's me.

555
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:37,760
You brat! How've you been?
You totally disappeared.

556
00:38:38,280 --> 00:38:41,800
Been busy lately,
a lot of studying and work to do.

557
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:44,440
And I've been a little under the weather.

558
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:46,880
How about you, Auntie? How are you?

559
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:49,480
I'm fine, strong as ever.

560
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:52,080
I went for a check-up already,
so don't worry.

561
00:38:52,600 --> 00:38:55,640
Has anyone called me?

562
00:38:55,720 --> 00:39:01,040
Oh, so the reason you're calling
is to ask about me or someone else?

563
00:39:01,120 --> 00:39:03,960
Well, I called you.

564
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:06,000
Of course I'm asking about you.

565
00:39:06,080 --> 00:39:07,760
So, you're not interested in Pie?

566
00:39:07,840 --> 00:39:08,760
Of course I am.

567
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:11,600
Well, you could've just asked directly.

568
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:13,960
- But I don't know anything about Pie.
- Huh?

569
00:39:14,040 --> 00:39:16,080
She hasn't called at all.

570
00:39:16,160 --> 00:39:18,640
By the way, it's been a while now.

571
00:39:18,720 --> 00:39:20,200
Haven't you let go yet?

572
00:39:21,040 --> 00:39:23,080
I haven't been thinking about letting go.

573
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:25,000
Once I graduate,

574
00:39:25,600 --> 00:39:28,160
<i>I won't be the same old Win with nothing.</i>

575
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:32,320
I'll go back to Pie
with a job and a future.

576
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:34,040
Having determination is good.

577
00:39:34,120 --> 00:39:37,600
But by the time you get back,
do you think Pie will be waiting for you?

578
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:39,720
I don't know.

579
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:43,600
But I'm not going to give up on her.

580
00:39:43,680 --> 00:39:44,800
Alright.

581
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:46,800
That's it for now.

582
00:39:56,960 --> 00:40:00,360
<i>People are drawn to each other</i>
<i>by the energy of longing</i>

583
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:02,600
<i>and attachment.</i>

584
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:06,040
<i>The more we miss someone</i>
<i>and feel connected to them,</i>

585
00:40:07,360 --> 00:40:09,880
<i>the stronger the pull between us.</i>

586
00:40:11,280 --> 00:40:14,360
<i>No matter how much time passes,</i>

587
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:17,120
<i>if we don't forget to think about them,</i>

588
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:19,640
<i>they'll never truly leave our thoughts.</i>

589
00:40:23,080 --> 00:40:25,600
<i>I believe love</i>
<i>is like a powerful driving force</i>

590
00:40:25,680 --> 00:40:27,800
<i>with enormous energy.</i>

591
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:31,880
<i>When you love someone,</i>

592
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:39,960
<i>it's like carrying</i>
<i>a ginat bucket of water during a fire.</i>

593
00:40:40,040 --> 00:40:43,120
<i>We can do so much more</i>
<i>than we ever thought.</i>

594
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:49,040
<i>It's like love takes you</i>
<i>to a new dimension of yourself</i>

595
00:40:50,400 --> 00:40:51,320
<i>that you wouldn't know</i>

596
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:55,040
<i>if you hadn't loved.</i>

597
00:40:57,400 --> 00:41:01,400
<i>So, when you love someone</i>
<i>and give everything to them,</i>

598
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:03,120
<i>it doesn't mean you're stupid.</i>

599
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:05,040
<i>But he also deceives me.</i>

600
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:07,200
<i>Now, I've switched from love to pure hate.</i>

601
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:08,800
<i>There you go.</i>

602
00:41:08,880 --> 00:41:12,040
<i>Hate can also draw people toward us.</i>

603
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:13,360
<i>Think about it.</i>

604
00:41:13,440 --> 00:41:17,000
<i>When we hate someone,</i>
<i>it means we're still interested, right?</i>

605
00:41:17,080 --> 00:41:19,040
<i>Don't lie to me now.</i>

606
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:22,040
<i>Are you still stalking</i>
<i>your ex's Facebook or Instagram?</i>

607
00:41:22,120 --> 00:41:24,080
<i>Oh, of course.</i>

608
00:41:24,160 --> 00:41:26,240
<i>When I saw him with his new partner,</i>
<i>it was so intense.</i>

609
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:28,880
<i>I want to call him</i>
<i>and yell at him right now.</i>

610
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:30,160
<i>Whoa, hold on.</i>

611
00:41:30,240 --> 00:41:32,480
<i>Calm down first. Here's the thing.</i>

612
00:41:34,520 --> 00:41:38,160
<i>You need to find balance and stay neutral.</i>

613
00:41:38,240 --> 00:41:42,240
<i>When you love someone deeply,</i>
<i>you suffer a lot, right?</i>

614
00:41:42,320 --> 00:41:45,880
<i>Now that you hate them,</i>
<i>it's even more painful.</i>

615
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:48,440
<i>I think you need to start fresh.</i>

616
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,800
<i>You need to find that neutral ground.</i>

617
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:53,720
<i>First, stop loving and stop hating.</i>

618
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:57,600
<i>Like I said, when you hate someone,</i>
<i>it still pulls them toward you.</i>

619
00:41:58,200 --> 00:42:01,800
<i>I think you need to start</i>
<i>by stopping the stalking of their life.</i>

620
00:42:01,880 --> 00:42:04,160
<i>Then, focus on your own life.</i>

621
00:42:05,960 --> 00:42:08,560
Exactly! Pek is right!

622
00:42:10,440 --> 00:42:11,440
Puk.

623
00:42:11,520 --> 00:42:12,640
Oh, yes?

624
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:16,320
Sorry, Miss Pie.

625
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:19,880
I didn't know you were a fan
of Pek's show too.

626
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:24,680
Miss Pie, this show is really good!

627
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:28,560
I like listening to it.
"Here's the thing."

628
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:31,800
It really hits home on a lot of things.

629
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:33,200
When they go live,

630
00:42:33,280 --> 00:42:36,000
they have thousands of listeners.

631
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:37,440
You should try listening too.

632
00:42:37,520 --> 00:42:39,520
It's really good!

633
00:42:39,600 --> 00:42:43,400
Maybe after listening,
you'll soften up and get a boyfriend.

634
00:42:45,880 --> 00:42:47,320
Where's Mom?

635
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:49,960
Over there, in the prayer room.

636
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:52,120
- Thanks.
- No problem.

637
00:43:23,680 --> 00:43:24,680
Pie.

638
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:28,320
What flaws do you see in Pun

639
00:43:28,840 --> 00:43:30,680
that you won't accept him
as your boyfriend?

640
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:37,160
There's nothing wrong with him.

641
00:43:37,680 --> 00:43:39,240
Pun is perfect.

642
00:43:39,960 --> 00:43:41,720
The reason I haven't accepted him

643
00:43:42,240 --> 00:43:44,280
is because I don't think
I'm good enough for him.

644
00:43:49,840 --> 00:43:52,840
What you're saying
is like you're insulting me,

645
00:43:52,920 --> 00:43:55,800
insulting Pun, and insulting
everyone who loves you.

646
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:59,960
If you're really not good enough,
does that mean the people who love you

647
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:01,920
are stupid and can't judge people?

648
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:04,520
And it makes it seem
like I've raised you badly,

649
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:07,920
so you're not worthy
of being loved by someone good?

650
00:44:08,680 --> 00:44:09,560
Pie.

651
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:12,640
I'm really asking you now.

652
00:44:13,680 --> 00:44:16,320
Do you still love or think
about that Win guy?

653
00:44:21,080 --> 00:44:21,920
No.

654
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:25,400
Sometimes it crosses my mind.

655
00:44:26,160 --> 00:44:28,840
But that man is definitely
not a factor anymore.

656
00:44:31,160 --> 00:44:34,160
I don't want to see him.
I don't want to be near him.

657
00:44:34,240 --> 00:44:36,400
I don't want to care
about someone like that anymore.

658
00:44:39,080 --> 00:44:40,280
That's a relief.

659
00:44:43,840 --> 00:44:44,880
Pie.

660
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:47,720
Having a good family

661
00:44:48,240 --> 00:44:50,240
isn't just about love.

662
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:52,640
It has to be about compatibility too.

663
00:44:53,840 --> 00:44:56,560
Everyone used to tell me
not to marry your father,

664
00:44:57,080 --> 00:44:59,720
but I believed in love.

665
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:02,680
In the end, I had nothing left, Pie.

666
00:45:04,240 --> 00:45:06,200
If I could turn back time,

667
00:45:06,760 --> 00:45:08,680
I would have listened to the adults.

668
00:45:09,720 --> 00:45:12,000
I don't have that chance anymore.

669
00:45:13,000 --> 00:45:14,560
But you still do.

670
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:19,840
And if you can't find any flaws in Pun,

671
00:45:20,440 --> 00:45:23,800
I don't see why you should reject him.

672
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:27,400
I want you to give yourself a chance

673
00:45:27,480 --> 00:45:29,760
and believe that you're good enough

674
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:32,640
to have a good man in your life.

675
00:45:33,240 --> 00:45:35,600
Don't let past mistakes

676
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:38,600
close off opportunities for you.

677
00:45:48,200 --> 00:45:49,480
Those words cut deep.

678
00:45:50,080 --> 00:45:52,000
I think your mom is right, Pie.

679
00:45:52,080 --> 00:45:54,600
If you can't find any flaws in Pun,

680
00:45:54,680 --> 00:45:56,800
why don't you just agree
to be his girlfriend?

681
00:45:57,400 --> 00:45:58,400
Hey.

682
00:45:58,480 --> 00:46:00,560
We should stop talking about me
and focus on you.

683
00:46:00,640 --> 00:46:03,760
Why did you bring me
to your boyfriend's cafe?

684
00:46:03,840 --> 00:46:05,280
Isn't it closed?

685
00:46:05,360 --> 00:46:06,920
Yeah.

686
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:09,040
- But lately, it's been weird.
- Huh?

687
00:46:09,120 --> 00:46:12,640
When I call, he takes forever to pick up
and then calls back late at night.

688
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,480
Is he busy or something?

689
00:46:14,560 --> 00:46:16,560
At first, I thought that was the case.

690
00:46:16,640 --> 00:46:20,400
So I brought you here. Look, it's closed.

691
00:46:20,920 --> 00:46:22,120
Something's off.

692
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:26,200
And when we were together,
he always got calls

693
00:46:26,280 --> 00:46:27,600
and he'd just hang up.

694
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:30,480
When I asked him why he didn't answer,

695
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:32,720
he said he wanted
to have quality time with me.

696
00:46:33,520 --> 00:46:35,200
That sounds so perfect.

697
00:46:35,280 --> 00:46:36,640
But I smell something fishy.

698
00:46:38,080 --> 00:46:41,400
If you really saw him with another woman,

699
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,520
what would you do?

700
00:46:44,600 --> 00:46:46,200
- I'd kill him!
- What?

701
00:46:46,280 --> 00:46:47,520
What are you doing, Rok?

702
00:46:48,040 --> 00:46:49,120
Wait!

703
00:46:55,080 --> 00:46:57,360
- Hey, Rok!
- I missed you.

704
00:46:57,440 --> 00:46:58,520
- Babe.
- Tay!

705
00:46:59,360 --> 00:47:00,400
Rok!

706
00:47:00,480 --> 00:47:01,680
You still remember my name?

707
00:47:01,760 --> 00:47:03,720
I thought your head was full of bad stuff.

708
00:47:03,800 --> 00:47:04,800
Just drop dead already!

709
00:47:04,880 --> 00:47:05,760
- Hey, Rok!
- Wait!

710
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:07,360
Calm down and let's talk first.

711
00:47:07,440 --> 00:47:10,320
We're all intelligent here.
Let's use reason in this conversation.

712
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:11,680
A person with reason

713
00:47:11,760 --> 00:47:14,600
doesn't date multiple people
and run away by turning off their phone.

714
00:47:15,720 --> 00:47:17,160
And you switch from me to…

715
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:19,760
this?

716
00:47:19,840 --> 00:47:20,960
No more talking.

717
00:47:21,040 --> 00:47:23,600
Just break up already! It's over!

718
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:26,400
But before we end it, let me hit you once.

719
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:27,880
- Rok, no!
- Hey, Rok!

720
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:29,240
- Rok, calm down!
- Stop!

721
00:47:30,360 --> 00:47:31,680
Rok!

722
00:47:33,240 --> 00:47:35,720
Rok! Rok!

723
00:47:35,800 --> 00:47:38,360
- Rok!
- Rok, stop!

724
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:41,480
- Rok!
- Rok, no!

725
00:47:44,920 --> 00:47:48,040
Hello, Pun? Rok needs urgent help!

726
00:47:48,560 --> 00:47:51,240
- Rok!
- Stop it, Rok!

727
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:53,600
PUBLIC SERVICE CENTER

728
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:55,600
Why are you paying for the damages?

729
00:47:55,680 --> 00:47:57,000
He cheated on me, you know.

730
00:47:57,080 --> 00:47:59,560
Rok, listen to me.

731
00:47:59,640 --> 00:48:03,240
You were just dating.
The law doesn't protect that.

732
00:48:03,320 --> 00:48:05,360
And you hurting him like that,

733
00:48:05,440 --> 00:48:07,960
it's good he didn't press more charges.

734
00:48:08,040 --> 00:48:11,280
But I'm so angry, Pun! He lied to me!

735
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:13,960
When he was trying to date me,
he said he liked tough people.

736
00:48:14,040 --> 00:48:15,800
But his new girlfriend isn't tough at all.

737
00:48:15,880 --> 00:48:19,040
- I don't get it.
- Hey, calm down.

738
00:48:19,120 --> 00:48:20,560
Let's go home first.

739
00:48:20,640 --> 00:48:23,400
Don't drive. I'll drive, okay?

740
00:48:24,680 --> 00:48:25,680
Pie, how about this?

741
00:48:25,760 --> 00:48:27,200
Let Rok go with me.

742
00:48:27,280 --> 00:48:30,200
You follow us in her car
and meet at her house, okay?

743
00:48:31,680 --> 00:48:32,760
Okay.

744
00:48:34,720 --> 00:48:37,160
- Thanks, Pie.
- Sure.

745
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:38,920
If you hadn't called Pun,

746
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:41,080
- I would've already killed that guy!
- Alright.

747
00:48:42,960 --> 00:48:44,240
- Let's go home.
- Let's go.

748
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:45,240
Let me see.

749
00:48:45,960 --> 00:48:48,640
How could he dump my beautiful sister?

750
00:49:05,480 --> 00:49:07,440
- Pun!
- Hey.

751
00:49:09,040 --> 00:49:11,000
There are so many other guys out there.

752
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:26,480
Krarok.

753
00:49:26,560 --> 00:49:27,920
Mom!

754
00:49:29,120 --> 00:49:30,960
- Hello, Auntie.
- Hello.

755
00:49:31,040 --> 00:49:34,240
Hi. It's okay. Don't worry.

756
00:49:34,320 --> 00:49:35,640
It's okay.

757
00:49:43,760 --> 00:49:45,960
Thank you so much for taking care of her.

758
00:49:46,040 --> 00:49:47,080
I'll handle her from here.

759
00:49:47,160 --> 00:49:51,400
Of course. If you need anything,
call me anytime.

760
00:49:51,480 --> 00:49:53,520
- Sure, thank you.
- No problem.

761
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:54,560
- Goodbye, Auntie.
- Bye.

762
00:49:54,640 --> 00:49:55,840
- Goodbye.
- Drive safely.

763
00:49:55,920 --> 00:49:57,160
Yes.

764
00:49:57,240 --> 00:49:59,960
- I'm leaving.
- Bye!

765
00:50:05,720 --> 00:50:09,000
If a guy's no good,
just dump him and be done with it.

766
00:50:09,080 --> 00:50:11,160
You can always find a new one, okay?

767
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:13,040
But I'm still mad, Mom.

768
00:50:13,120 --> 00:50:14,320
Mad?

769
00:50:14,400 --> 00:50:15,960
Want me to get revenge for you?

770
00:50:16,040 --> 00:50:17,960
- Let's go!
- Hey, wait.

771
00:50:18,040 --> 00:50:19,840
I'm kidding.

772
00:50:19,920 --> 00:50:23,760
- Mom!
- Calm down. It's okay.

773
00:50:27,800 --> 00:50:28,800
Pun.

774
00:50:30,200 --> 00:50:31,080
Yes?

775
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:35,800
Well…

776
00:50:42,120 --> 00:50:44,240
Do you still want the same flower

777
00:50:45,040 --> 00:50:49,960
that you once said you liked
for your vase?

778
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:57,880
My vase never wavers.

779
00:50:59,320 --> 00:51:01,000
It doesn't change its mind easily.

780
00:51:03,120 --> 00:51:04,040
So,

781
00:51:05,400 --> 00:51:06,920
is this flower

782
00:51:08,360 --> 00:51:10,640
ready to go in the vase now?

783
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:17,280
If you aren't tired of my indecisiveness

784
00:51:17,880 --> 00:51:20,000
and aren't exhausted
from taking care of me,

785
00:51:20,800 --> 00:51:21,800
then…

786
00:51:23,880 --> 00:51:24,840
yes.

787
00:51:24,920 --> 00:51:26,480
Yes!

788
00:51:29,680 --> 00:51:32,560
Now that you've agreed
to be my girlfriend,

789
00:51:32,640 --> 00:51:34,120
what about furthering your studies?

790
00:51:37,560 --> 00:51:41,160
I'll give up my scholarship
and continue working with you.

791
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:53,080
I promise
I'll take care of everything for you.

792
00:51:53,160 --> 00:51:55,360
I'll take care of you the best I can.

793
00:51:55,440 --> 00:51:59,120
I promise you won't regret it.
You won't feel bad for choosing me.

794
00:52:02,920 --> 00:52:04,160
Pun.

795
00:52:04,800 --> 00:52:06,000
Okay, Pun.

796
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:08,120
Wait a second, please.

797
00:52:09,320 --> 00:52:11,240
You're hugging me a bit too tight.

798
00:52:12,120 --> 00:52:13,680
- Sorry.
- It's fine.

799
00:52:13,760 --> 00:52:16,480
Sorry. I'm just…

800
00:52:17,240 --> 00:52:19,040
really happy and excited.

801
00:52:23,240 --> 00:52:27,080
Pie, now that we're officially together,

802
00:52:27,160 --> 00:52:30,480
I have an important task,
and I'd like your help.

803
00:52:31,680 --> 00:52:35,760
If it's work, I'll still do it,
even if we're not dating.

804
00:52:35,840 --> 00:52:37,560
I'm your employee, after all.

805
00:52:38,320 --> 00:52:40,640
But this task isn't like the usual ones.

806
00:52:40,720 --> 00:52:41,960
It's really important.

807
00:52:42,920 --> 00:52:44,280
What kind of task is it?

808
00:52:50,920 --> 00:52:53,360
I'd like you to introduce
this fabric to the client.

809
00:52:53,440 --> 00:52:55,760
- Yes.
- Show them that we have the knowledge

810
00:52:55,840 --> 00:52:57,840
and are true experts.

811
00:52:57,920 --> 00:53:00,480
Sure. I've worked on some information
about this fabric,

812
00:53:00,560 --> 00:53:01,760
so I remember it.

813
00:53:02,920 --> 00:53:05,280
How many clients will be listening today?

814
00:53:05,360 --> 00:53:06,880
Do I have time to prepare a presentation?

815
00:53:07,520 --> 00:53:09,920
No need. There's only one client.

816
00:53:10,640 --> 00:53:11,800
- Just one?
- Yep.

817
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:18,120
Pun, with a house like this,

818
00:53:18,200 --> 00:53:20,080
they can't just be an ordinary person.

819
00:53:20,600 --> 00:53:22,320
Will they listen to someone like me?

820
00:53:25,320 --> 00:53:26,920
You'll find out soon. Let's go.

821
00:53:27,000 --> 00:53:27,960
Yes.

822
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:37,120
This piece is a golden brocade skirt
with the Phimsen pattern.

823
00:53:37,200 --> 00:53:40,320
It's a renowned fabric from ancient times.

824
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:44,040
Its distinctiveness
lies in its beauty and high value.

825
00:53:44,120 --> 00:53:48,160
This golden brocade skirt is woven
from fine Thai silk threads,

826
00:53:48,240 --> 00:53:52,000
dyed with natural colors
using traditional methods.

827
00:53:52,080 --> 00:53:54,240
The patterns are woven with gold thread

828
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:56,360
made from precious metals,

829
00:53:56,440 --> 00:53:57,960
which are very small

830
00:53:58,040 --> 00:54:01,360
and custom-made from France and India.

831
00:54:02,040 --> 00:54:04,920
This ensures the fabric
is thin, soft, and smooth,

832
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:08,080
yet dense, and drapes
beautifully when worn.

833
00:54:08,160 --> 00:54:10,840
If you look closely
at the center of the fabric,

834
00:54:10,920 --> 00:54:16,200
you'll see a geometric pattern
of tiny, delicate diamond-shaped crystals.

835
00:54:16,280 --> 00:54:19,720
This pattern is called
the Phimsen pattern by the ancients.

836
00:54:19,800 --> 00:54:21,760
You speak fluently.

837
00:54:21,840 --> 00:54:24,480
Which shop do you sell fabric at?
I'll go support you.

838
00:54:30,840 --> 00:54:34,480
I don't sell fabric. I work with Pun.

839
00:54:36,480 --> 00:54:39,520
So you work for Pun? What's your position?

840
00:54:39,600 --> 00:54:41,280
I'm in the information department.

841
00:54:41,360 --> 00:54:44,960
I gather information and develop content
to be displayed in the museum.

842
00:54:45,680 --> 00:54:46,760
And she's my girlfriend.

843
00:54:48,280 --> 00:54:49,280
Girlfriend?

844
00:54:49,920 --> 00:54:52,520
Yes, Mom. Pie is my girlfriend.

845
00:54:54,040 --> 00:54:55,000
Mom?

846
00:54:56,680 --> 00:54:59,600
Yes, Pie. This is my mom,
and that's my dad.

847
00:55:04,360 --> 00:55:05,640
Pie is Rok's friend.

848
00:55:05,720 --> 00:55:09,080
I met her at university while helping Phu
with the students' graduation project.

849
00:55:09,880 --> 00:55:13,680
Pie did a great job,
so I invited her to work with me.

850
00:55:14,360 --> 00:55:15,720
Then I asked her to be my girlfriend.

851
00:55:15,800 --> 00:55:18,720
And now she's agreed.

852
00:55:19,320 --> 00:55:21,680
So I wanted to introduce her to you.

853
00:55:23,000 --> 00:55:25,160
You made an employee your girlfriend?

854
00:55:25,760 --> 00:55:26,600
Yes.

855
00:55:27,880 --> 00:55:29,400
Pie is my employee.

856
00:55:30,040 --> 00:55:32,080
We have an age gap of over ten years,

857
00:55:32,160 --> 00:55:34,400
but I don't want to waste time anymore.

858
00:55:34,480 --> 00:55:36,080
I believe Pie is the right person for me.

859
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:37,880
I'm going to marry her.

860
00:55:37,960 --> 00:55:39,280
What?

861
00:55:39,360 --> 00:55:40,920
- Marry?
- Marry?

862
00:55:42,160 --> 00:55:43,320
Yes.

863
00:55:43,960 --> 00:55:44,960
That's right.

864
00:55:46,800 --> 00:55:49,440
- Nhun!
- Mom!

865
00:55:49,520 --> 00:55:52,120
- Mom!
- Nhun!

866
00:55:53,440 --> 00:55:54,320
Nhun!

867
00:55:57,160 --> 00:56:00,280
How are you? Are you okay?

868
00:56:03,040 --> 00:56:05,080
Are you getting up? Let me help.

869
00:56:07,040 --> 00:56:08,200
How are you feeling?

870
00:56:08,840 --> 00:56:10,600
She's alright now.

871
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:13,120
Am I dreaming, or is this real?

872
00:56:14,720 --> 00:56:16,080
If you're referring to Pun

873
00:56:16,160 --> 00:56:19,840
bringing his girlfriend to introduce her
and asking to marry her,

874
00:56:20,360 --> 00:56:22,160
you're not dreaming, it's real.

875
00:56:22,240 --> 00:56:25,120
Do you think you're going to faint again?

876
00:56:26,360 --> 00:56:27,720
I'm not going to faint anymore.

877
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:32,480
But where's Pun? Go get him right now.

878
00:56:33,320 --> 00:56:34,680
Calm down a bit first.

879
00:56:34,760 --> 00:56:36,800
How can I stay calm?

880
00:56:36,880 --> 00:56:40,320
Your son picks up some girl
from who knows where to marry.

881
00:56:40,400 --> 00:56:42,320
Suddenly announces
he has a girlfriend and plans to marry.

882
00:56:43,120 --> 00:56:44,360
This is crazy!

883
00:56:45,800 --> 00:56:46,840
Haven't you heard?

884
00:56:46,920 --> 00:56:50,280
Falling in love is a kind of madness.

885
00:56:50,360 --> 00:56:53,440
And it looks like
Pun is pretty deep in it.

886
00:56:55,040 --> 00:56:56,640
How deep can it really be?

887
00:56:56,720 --> 00:56:58,760
I'm the one who's going to dig him out.

888
00:56:59,400 --> 00:57:03,080
It's too fast.
I won't let them get married.

889
00:57:06,400 --> 00:57:08,320
Why didn't you talk to me first, Pun?

890
00:57:08,400 --> 00:57:11,480
You brought me to meet your mom
and talked marriage without telling me.

891
00:57:12,240 --> 00:57:13,880
I didn't want to waste time, Pie.

892
00:57:14,760 --> 00:57:17,480
It took so many days for you
to agree to be my girlfriend.

893
00:57:18,040 --> 00:57:20,440
If I told you I was bringing you
to meet my parents,

894
00:57:20,520 --> 00:57:23,760
you'd ask for time to think about it,

895
00:57:24,520 --> 00:57:25,440
right?

896
00:57:28,360 --> 00:57:31,800
- Yes, but…
- That's why I brought you here right away.

897
00:57:33,360 --> 00:57:34,640
As for marriage,

898
00:57:35,880 --> 00:57:38,880
I didn't want you to feel uncomfortable
with what my mom said.

899
00:57:41,280 --> 00:57:44,960
I want you to see
that I'm serious and sincere.

900
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:48,960
That's why I said it in front of my mom,

901
00:57:49,840 --> 00:57:51,360
to make things clear.

902
00:57:55,760 --> 00:57:57,800
Pun and Pie.

903
00:57:58,400 --> 00:57:59,720
- Mom wants to talk to you.
- Yes?

904
00:58:02,760 --> 00:58:03,720
Alright.

905
00:58:15,800 --> 00:58:17,200
<i>I don't like that girl.</i>

906
00:58:17,280 --> 00:58:18,640
<i>I don't want her as my daughter-in-law.</i>

907
00:58:18,720 --> 00:58:22,080
If his mom doesn't like you,
why should you care, Pie?

908
00:58:22,160 --> 00:58:24,400
But she's his mom.
How can we not care, Mom?

909
00:58:24,480 --> 00:58:26,440
<i>Even if Mom doesn't accept her,</i>
<i>she can't stop me.</i>

910
00:58:26,520 --> 00:58:28,080
Pie is the one I've chosen.

911
00:58:28,160 --> 00:58:29,880
Is she pregnant?

912
00:58:29,960 --> 00:58:31,800
Seriously, did you get her pregnant?

913
00:58:31,880 --> 00:58:34,000
I don't understand
why everyone keeps asking this.

914
00:58:34,080 --> 00:58:37,160
I didn't raise my daughter
to sell her off.

915
00:58:37,240 --> 00:58:38,600
- I said no.
- Let me see.

916
00:58:38,680 --> 00:58:39,560
- Mom.
- No need to.

917
00:58:39,640 --> 00:58:40,800
Let me see!

918
00:58:40,880 --> 00:58:42,280
<i>Why didn't you talk to me first, Pun?</i>

919
00:58:42,360 --> 00:58:44,080
I didn't want to waste time, Pie.

920
00:58:44,160 --> 00:58:46,960
Pie's going to marry my brother.

921
00:58:47,040 --> 00:58:49,240
<i>I'm sure Pun loves you a lot.</i>

922
00:58:49,320 --> 00:58:50,280
Nhun!

923
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:52,480
<i>Everything will work out just fine.</i>

924
00:59:15,640 --> 00:59:20,240
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
